25
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:05,800
[choral singing]

26
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:11,840
â™ª â™ª

27
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:15,620
[upbeat rock music]

28
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:45,580
[MUSIC]

29
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,120
(dramatic music)

30
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,240
Experimentation?

31
00:03:34,060 --> 00:03:38,260
They were running a project that would turn the children into perfect soldiers.

32
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,320
Mental reconstruction.

33
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:45,100
Twisting their minds for science.

34
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:55,400
They made the children form factions to observe the aggression, the fighting, and the hate that resulted.

35
00:03:56,160 --> 00:04:02,340
It was an experiment to claw every last bit of compassion out of those children and see what remained.

36
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:09,220
Can you imagine what kind of adults those children grew up to be?

37
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:15,080
And now the problem is there's no way to prove that anything like that ever went on.

38
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:20,760
Any type of data or secret records, all those documents were burned before the wall fell.

39
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:25,520
Everyone who had anything at all to do with the project fled the country.

40
00:04:27,580 --> 00:04:31,240
However, I've heard rumors of someone who remained.

41
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,960
He managed to clean his records.

42
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:37,960
He stayed even though he was the last person in the world who deserved a second chance.

43
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:44,940
He was the man who was in charge of overseeing the abomination that was 511 Kinderheim.

44
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:52,220
And even though he was actually a pediatric psychiatrist closely affiliated with the Ministry of the Interior Police,

45
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:57,340
the man's real title was that of a district official with the Ministry of Welfare.

46
00:04:57,620 --> 00:05:01,960
A district official... with the Ministry of Welfare...

47
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:09,500
Inga, are you all done in the bathroom?

48
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,920
Sweet dreams, honey.

49
00:05:12,860 --> 00:05:13,340
All right?

50
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:15,200
Good night.

51
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:16,640
Good night.

52
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:22,120
They were careful to cover everything up.

53
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:24,960
Especially after that incident.

54
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,840
Incident? Tell me.

55
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:30,480
I need to know what exactly happened at 511 Kinderheim.

56
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:35,500
I've said too much already. Such horrible memories.

57
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:39,180
But I have to know! You must tell me what happened there, please!

58
00:05:45,460 --> 00:05:46,840
Where's my soccer ball?

59
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:47,800
Huh?

60
00:05:49,060 --> 00:05:51,820
Where is it? Do you know where my soccer ball went to?

61
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,020
Oh!

62
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:00,300
Here you go. I have it right here.

63
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:07,120
But you gotta hold off on soccer until your wounds heal, alright?

64
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,380
That man who brought you in earlier said he was going to pick you up soon.

65
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:14,240
You just get some rest until then, 'kay?

66
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:19,620
I don't know what really happened there.

67
00:06:20,620 --> 00:06:21,540
No one does.

68
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:26,220
The East German government at the time placed a strict gag order on the event.

69
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:31,780
It all began with the mysterious death of the director of 5-1-1 Kinderheim.

70
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:38,000
Soon after, there was a power struggle among the instructors there as to who would succeed him.

71
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:42,740
The place was thrown into anarchy. It was utter chaos.

72
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:47,520
They couldn't even control the children. It was every man for himself.

73
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:50,740
It's a miracle Johann made it out of there alive.

74
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:55,180
Then what? What exactly happened at 5-1-1 Kinderheim?

75
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:57,720
What?

76
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:02,320
All of the instructors and every last orphan except Johan.

77
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:05,120
Those people massacred each other.

78
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:18,040
The world's not a dark place, that's a lie.

79
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:22,080
Tomorrow will be a good day, I promise.

80
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:26,080
Dieter, time to gather up your things, honey.

81
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:27,160
[nervous chuckle]

82
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,280
Excuse me, Mr. Hartman, but...

83
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,380
aren't we going to go home now?

84
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:55,500
No. We're taking a little detour.

85
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,640
But I don't want to go back there.

86
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,820
No! No! I don't want to go!

87
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:11,220
Eater?

88
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:15,720
Eater, come on now. Be a good boy.

89
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,080
What do you mean?

90
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:33,560
I told you not to let Dieter leave with anyone until I came back, didn't I?

91
00:08:33,660 --> 00:08:34,800
But all I did was...

92
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:37,560
That person was the child's foster father.

93
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:41,380
And let me tell you, he was very much a gentleman.

94
00:08:41,940 --> 00:08:43,380
Unlike you, obviously.

95
00:08:46,340 --> 00:08:48,340
Look, I'm sorry, but that man...

96
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:49,660
I wouldn't worry.

97
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:53,540
That boy seemed very happy to be going with him.

98
00:09:01,020 --> 00:09:01,660
Dina!

99
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:16,700
Dina, I'm here!

100
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:26,120
Dieter?

101
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:31,220
They're not back yet.

102
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:39,340
Hartmann's library...

103
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:39,760
(microwave beeping)

104
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:24,380
These photos were taken at different times, but they were all shot at the same location.

105
00:10:24,380 --> 00:10:26,700
So what am I looking at?

106
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:38,720
Johan...

107
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:44,660
Who's the man in the photo next to him?

108
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:50,640
Yes, that's it.

109
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:55,280
Every single one of these photographs was taken at 511 Kinderheim.

110
00:10:56,540 --> 00:10:59,400
And it looks like they were taken over ten years ago.

111
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:05,300
All of the instructors and every last orphan except Johan.

112
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:08,080
Those people massacred each other.

113
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:15,180
Dieter. Could he be another?

114
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:23,400
[MUSIC FADES OUT]

115
00:11:31,020 --> 00:11:32,160
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

116
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:37,380
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

117
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:39,680
Deidre!

118
00:12:43,340 --> 00:12:44,800
Just hold on, Deidre!

119
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:45,660
I'm coming!

120
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:55,900
This child is blind to what I show him.

121
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:56,700
Hartman!

122
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,540
He can't see it.

123
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:03,060
He can't even comprehend what Johan saw.

124
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:05,420
He's not like him.

125
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:09,680
It's no good.

126
00:13:10,540 --> 00:13:11,940
It has failed again.

127
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:15,160
This boy is no Johan.

128
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:26,400
Every single one of them died here, did you know that?

129
00:13:30,260 --> 00:13:35,840
Ten years ago, the instructors and the orphans,

130
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,840
all 50 people died.

131
00:13:43,420 --> 00:13:46,680
Johan sat here, just watching it all happen.

132
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:51,580
He just sat here and watched everything.

133
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:04,980
He didn't lift a finger. He just watched.

134
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:14,960
I had to know his secret.

135
00:14:17,020 --> 00:14:22,760
So I asked Johan what he'd done and this was how he answered.

136
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:28,880
He dropped a piece of oil-soaked cloth into the fire, like this.

137
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:42,120
Do you get it? Do you know what he meant by that?

138
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:48,280
I simply added a bit of fuel to the hatred born when people come together.

139
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:50,000
It was easy.

140
00:14:52,140 --> 00:14:53,340
That's what he told me.

141
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:56,220
Only ten years old and he said that.

142
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:59,920
And he did it with almost no effort at all.

143
00:15:00,340 --> 00:15:05,260
He was able to make fifty people kill each other without even moving a finger.

144
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:08,040
It was you.

145
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:13,580
It was you and your damned experiments that twisted Johan into what he is!

146
00:15:15,060 --> 00:15:16,240
So you think it was us?

147
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:19,960
I'm sorry, it wasn't us at all.

148
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,200
We didn't make him that way.

149
00:15:23,020 --> 00:15:27,540
It's true that 511 Kinderheim was an experimental project,

150
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:31,860
specifically created to transform orphans into perfect soldiers.

151
00:15:32,780 --> 00:15:36,360
Thinking back on it now, it really was only a little experiment.

152
00:15:38,140 --> 00:15:46,620
Johan? He's no soldier. Not at all. He was better. He was a natural-born leader of men.

153
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:51,700
Someone who was meant to stand at the very top of the world. There's no way we could

154
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:59,060
have ever created such a work of art. He was beyond human from the beginning. A veritable

155
00:15:59,060 --> 00:16:05,260
monster. Johan made a prediction. He predicted that

156
00:16:05,260 --> 00:16:12,380
Mankind would end up hating itself into oblivion and what do you think Johan's goal was?

157
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,400
Do you want to know what he told me?

158
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:22,080
He said he wanted to be the last person left in this world he did

159
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:42,480
My poor Dieter. The future is dark. You must try harder to become more like Johan.

160
00:16:44,180 --> 00:16:45,600
It's a pity.

161
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:51,500
Why are you such a failure?

162
00:16:56,020 --> 00:16:58,240
Why can't you be more like Yohan?

163
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:00,080
Tell me why!

164
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,440
Drop the gun or I'll shoot!

165
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:04,660
Don't you lay a finger on him, Hartmann!

166
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,620
Get out of here.

167
00:17:08,120 --> 00:17:09,180
This is our problem.

168
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,780
It's none of your business.

169
00:17:11,320 --> 00:17:12,100
Just leave!

170
00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:12,820
Dieter!

171
00:17:12,820 --> 00:17:14,540
Come down from there!

172
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:17,760
Sorry, Dr. Tenma.

173
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:19,900
That's right.

174
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,820
You were wanting to know more about Johan.

175
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:27,260
What were you planning to do once you knew more?

176
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:30,960
When you find Johan, are you going to try and kill him?

177
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,220
That will be impossible.

178
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:37,080
Don't look so mad.

179
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:39,800
I'm going to let you in on a little secret.

180
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:45,100
But in exchange, once you hear it, you must leave immediately and never come back.

181
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:58,320
You should search out a General Wolf.

182
00:17:59,020 --> 00:18:02,220
He's the one who first discovered Johann and his abilities.

183
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:04,980
I'm sure he's still alive somewhere.

184
00:18:04,980 --> 00:18:09,180
So is he the man in the photograph? The one in your study?

185
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:12,200
Is General Wolf the man standing next to Johan?

186
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:17,760
He's the one who brought Johan to us. He should be able to tell you something.

187
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:20,200
Now, get going.

188
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:22,640
Dieter!

189
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:28,220
You can come with me or stay here, but you have to decide for yourself.

190
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:33,040
There's nothing to worry about!

191
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:36,320
If Hartmann does anything to try and stop you, I'll shoot him!

192
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,540
Dieter, listen to me.

193
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:46,740
The choice is your own.

194
00:18:47,260 --> 00:18:48,960
Nobody else can make it for you.

195
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:55,360
Go ahead, tell the doctor.

196
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:57,120
There's no way you'd leave me.

197
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:02,260
You can't live without me, because you're my child, Dieter.

198
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:09,780
Now you see how it is, Dr. Tenma.

199
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:11,560
You can leave.

200
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,740
Where are you going?

201
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:41,760
It's all right.

202
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,040
It's okay.

203
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,720
That's good.

204
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,520
Nice and slow.

205
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:48,280
Dieter!

206
00:19:48,740 --> 00:19:49,880
Come back here!

207
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,320
My dear little Dieter!

208
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:52,740
Dieter!

209
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:56,760
Do you really think you can live without me?

210
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:58,200
No, Dieter!

211
00:19:58,220 --> 00:20:00,480
Make a move, and I'll shoot, Hartmann.

212
00:20:01,020 --> 00:20:03,140
I love you so much, Dieter.

213
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:04,900
Dieter!

214
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:08,120
The world is dark.

215
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:10,720
The future is bleak, Dieter.

216
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:17,100
It's not true. Tenma told me.

217
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:19,640
Tomorrow will be a good day.

218
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,820
Dieter, he's wrong!

219
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:26,940
Be brave, Dieter.

220
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,600
(sobbing)

221
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:45,900
- Dieter, my boy!

222
00:20:46,860 --> 00:20:47,720
Dieter!

223
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,500
Dieter!

224
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:56,620
Dieter!

225
00:21:02,540 --> 00:21:03,000
(sobbing)

226
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:12,460
- Get on the bus here and take it to Kunin Street.

227
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:13,440
You got that?

228
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:17,080
The orphanage is there by the bus stop.

229
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:18,640
When you get there,

230
00:21:18,740 --> 00:21:21,000
I want you to give this letter to Elna Tice.

231
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,280
She runs the orphanage.

232
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:25,960
I know she may look scary, but she's a nice lady.

233
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:34,580
"Be a good boy, okay? I can't stay in this town anymore, so I guess this is goodbye.

234
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:41,520
The bus will be along in a few minutes. Take care, Dieter. Keep up the soccer practice."

235
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:55,820
I'm sorry.

236
00:21:56,260 --> 00:21:57,400
You can't come with me.

237
00:21:58,100 --> 00:21:58,340
Here.

238
00:22:04,380 --> 00:22:06,820
Dieter, I'm telling you, don't come with me.

239
00:22:06,820 --> 00:22:08,720
I'm serious, okay?

240
00:22:15,660 --> 00:22:17,540
You can't come with me, Dieter.

241
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,360
[MUSIC]

242
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:40,700
(gentle music)

